definitions.definition: The pharaonic patriarch who led the enslaved Hebrews out of Egypt, the brother of Aaron and Miriam described in the Book of Exodus and the Quran .
A male given name from Hebrew .
A surname transferred from the given name .
A dialect of the Columbia-Wenatchi language
